reviews.review_text: Good rustic Cantonese food at good prices. Place is not pretty but clean. Highly recommend to pre order their roast goose ahead of time.

This is a place with integrity. We ordered food on line and due to my error we had to cancel the order. One month later they credited our card for the full amount when Master Card refused to help us. Thank you K & H Seafood  we look forward to eating at your Restaurant the next time we are in Vancouver
Friendly staff. Yummy food. Big portion. Deep fried chicken is a must try and it comes with shrimp chips too!!
This has always been my goto place for Chinese food.   They always hit the spot, good prices and I have never had a bad experience from here.
Great deal and delicious Deep Fried Squab (ask for uncut to keep juicy and warm if takeout). Dont miss this item.
Gotta come here for the king crab with a large group! Super delicious and fresh
Good taste but bad air conditioner
If you are looking for an old school Cantonese restaurant with great food and big portions this is the place. Came here once on a family members recommendation and now I am a regular.
Excellent food with a reasonable price. I discovered it during cocoa do Ive only had takeout so far but its been consistently great.
This is always my to go restaurant. Price is economic and portion is decent. It might not be the finest, but it always fill my belly well.
Food is excellent and portion size remains unchanged big, restaurant itself didnt have any renovation for a long time, otherwise nothing can complain to the food itself
Good price and portion. The steam fish that goes with the meal is so fresh it is hard to believe its a bonus item.
Take out combination dinners are 12 bucks and fill your belly...delicious...i wouldnt go anywhere else for that price.
Family style Chinese food. Reasonable price and good quality. Some unique dishes
Rose Garden on Kingsway Vancouver has great food. The shrimp is fresh and nice portions too.
Solid late night food. Been coming here for years and they are very friendly. Great seafood too!
My local chinese joint. Order from here monthly. Just not a fan of the wonton soup.
Consistently great food.  The aroma in the restaurant and packed house testifies to their great food.
Great food for a great price!  Friendly staff!
Good quality and reasonable price.  One of my all time favorite.
Food is really good.  Very traditional chinese seafood restaurant
Great price, big portions, and good food
One of the best chinese places I have been too
The best place for Chinese food you wont be disappointed
Food is surprisingly good, portions as well!
Best apricot pork chop.
Great late night and go too for late Chinese food!
Fish and Seafood are awesome. Highly recommended
Good food, good prices
Good quality food.
Great food!

Vegetarian options: Best Chinese food Ive had in years Vegetarian options were well recieved by vegetarian family and I must say their Kung pou chicken, beef/broccoli with blackbean sauce, almond chicken,  were great. I have been searching for the chicken chow mein of my youth and they nailed it, just moved   here and will be a regular customer for sure, glad my neighbor recommended it  .
Its very good
Great lobster!
Lovely food
Ho sik ahhhhh. Ho bao ahhhhh
reviews.review_translated_text: Ho sik ahhhhh. Ho bao ahhhhh.

reviews.review_text: Its a Chinese restaurant, but there are a lot of people. The lobster is delicious. The quantity is also large.
The place is big, the environment is good, the food is cheap, the price is good, and it is full every day.
good
Very satisfied
taste of home

The restaurant has a traditional Chinese vibe. The food is great We ordered lobster ($35/lb), cod fillet with corn cream (~$23), spicy Chinese eggplant, and two other dishes that I forgot the names. But these ones that I named were great. There were some options for group of 10 people for a good price too. There are some parking spots in the street beside as well as at the back of building if you can t park in Kingsway right in front of the restaurant. Parking: There are some spots in the street beside as well as at the back of building if you can t park in Kingsway right in front of the restaurant.
Great pricing for food and quality is usually on point. Could use some renovation work and service is good.

One of local go-to restaurants when were looking for some classic Chinese dishes. We often used to visit when they were called Rose Garden back in the day. The owners changed (I think) but the name on the menu still bears the old Rose Garden name. Not so much of a hidden gem as this place was busy when we visited. Nice that they have live seafood available. The lobster in ginger and green onion sauce on noodles was really good. The interior decor isnt fussy. Good option for take-out too.
Excellent cuisine. Large servings. Fair prices. Parking could be busy during mealtimes.
Decent Chinese restaurant, but looks like you need to be a local to know what they are good at.  Busy place with lots of returned customers.
Very good tradition Cantonese food! The interior was a bit tired but the food was good and service was prompt. Would definitely return!

Our family always goes here because its a convenient location, fast service and fair prices. They pretty much make all of the Chinese and Asian cuisine favourites, and you cant go wrong with anybody them
Good Chinese food, reasonable prices, and large dishes. Staff were also very nice.

Visited this restaurant this week.  Formerly known as Rose Garden.  Food was fantastic, despite being packed with customers our dishes came out in a timely manner.  Seafood (fish and crab) tasted fresh, other dishes were very tasty.  To boost my rating to a 5star they really needed an extra server to serve drinks and maybe to clean up a bit better. We got everything we asked for but getting the attention of a server was difficult at times. Price was more than fair compared to other Chinese restaurants in the area. Must try
Good country style food. Reasonably priced.

Cozy simply place with no fancy deco. Took our friends there (15 of us around one table!) and had an amazing experience. Servers do not talk much but they are actually very nice friendly people. Their BBQ pigeon is our favorite dish, highly recommend!!
Rose Garden changed name to K&H due to copyright infringement.   Same restaurant, same management.  Place looks like a hole in the wall but food is decent and worth going to.

Good fresh food ... and fast.  Ive been ordering from here for years.  Love the BBQ pork fried rice.  And the wonton soup has a heavenly broth.  Good clean, fresh food.  (Rarely greasy.)  Remember to ask for the free pop that comes with your order.

Ordered vegetable tofu pot.  It was tasty consider it was requested to be cooked without both msg and sugar.  The service was on point. The price was a little over my expectation, $15.70 including gst. I would recommend this place.
Its not a good looking place but foods are not bad people are friendly prices its fair street parking only thought.

While I was in the area, I would only order chinese take out from this place. the portions are great,t he quality is fantastic, some of the best rice and noodles I have ever had (get the BBQ pork fried rice and chao mien, the chicken and broccoli with black bean sauce is to die for!) you even get 10% off if you pic up your food from the restaurant! when I had to move from the area I was supper bummed that I couldnt walk here to get my orders despite this I still try to order from here when ever I have the craving for Chinese food
This place closes late. Good food and beer. Not very appropriate for wheelchair. Maybe one if there is space by the entrance. Decent prices. Park on the street. Not a fancy place but comfortable.
Best price for deep fried pigeon 15$ each (most Chinese delicacies) set dinner was good 6 dishes youll get a free life crab
Opens late till midnight. Great spot when hungry. Food is delicious. Recommended the pork chops in apricot sauce. Priced reasonable.
Classic HK style family diner. Good seafood and prices to boot. go with a large group and enjoy this place family style including lobster three ways.

Great place for a cheap dinner for a group. Even better for Chinese late night snack called Dai Lan. If you are not Chinese, ask for the Dai Lan menu after 930-10pm it consist of smaller dishes and if you order enough you get free congee.
Fabulous cuisine, innovative dishes, reasonable prices. Decoration could use some upgrade. However not much to complain value for money.
This is a great little well known fact that this is one of the best Chinese restaurants in town the food is fresh and of good quality, I have been coming back this restaurant for close to 25years !!
so cheap. 8 dishes cost only 125CAD and have a big free can of rice. However, service is not good enough
Great place for a late night congee.
Good foods with good prices. Only not so goods are: street parking and slow service from staff.
Food taste great at a reasonable price but can use some updating.
